`useDefineForClassFields` needs to be turned on, as class fields in esnext are emitted functionally that way, even though they just appear in the class definition, and `useDefineForClassFields` causes tsc to report some errors.

[`tsc`/check emits](https://www.typescriptlang.org/play?useDefineForClassFields=true&emitDecoratorMetadata=false&target=99#code/GYVwdgxgLglg9mABAIwIYCcAUB9KGDmAplAFyLgDWYcA7mADSLYWECeZAzlOjGPgJRlUYVogDeAKESJ0xEOiSTp0gG6oANiEJkALACYpiAL4SThAB4AHOOiiII61Bw6IAguMMABNOkPA4cAD8ZGAgALbIhOgA3KYSEAgccOqEAHTqcPiYYIQ0bpj8qf5w-LFAA):

```js
